In a large saucepan, cook carrots and/or beans in a small amount of boiling salted water for 10 minutes. Add the broccoli, sweet pepper, zucchini or yellow summer squash, and/or asparagus. Return to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and cook 3 minutes more or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Drain. Meanwhile, in a Dutch oven or large pot cook pasta according to package directions. Drain; return to Dutch oven. Add the vegetable mixture to the Dutch oven and keep warm while preparing sauce. For sauce, in a medium saucepan, cook onion and garlic in hot butter over medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until tender. In a medium bowl using a whisk, stir together LACTAID(R) Reduced Fat Milk, flour, salt, and black pepper. Add to onion mixture in saucepan. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir for 1 minute more. Stir in the prosciutto and basil. Pour sauce over pasta and vegetables. Toss gently to coat.